EXERCISE 1 — Jenkins CI/CD using Git Webhook

Step-1:
To install ngrok → Go to:
Settings → Privacy and Security → Windows Security → Turn OFF antivirus.

Step-2:
Go to https://ngrok.com → Signup using name, email, password (min 10 characters).

Step-3:
After signing in → Download ngrok for Windows (64-bit).

Step-4:
Extract the downloaded file → Click on ngrok.exe  
Ngrok command prompt opens.

Step-5: Connect Your ngrok Account
Go to your ngrok Authtoken page.  
Copy the Authtoken.

Run in ngrok command prompt:
ngrok config add-authtoken <your_token>

Example:
ngrok config add-authtoken 34ejJvRYKqtjvBUEYEnxudIbpb7_33i6pYx8BJ2cZ1TpwasWq

Step-6: Start Tunnel for Jenkins
Check Jenkins running port → open browser → localhost:8081  
Run in ngrok terminal:
ngrok http 8081

Copy the PUBLIC URL generated by ngrok.

Step-7: Configure Webhook in GitHub
Go to:
Repository → Settings → Webhooks → Add Webhook

Payload URL:
http://<your-ngrok-url>/github-webhook/

Example:
https://unhired-stormily-alaine.ngrok-free.dev/github-webhook/

Step-8:
Set Content Type:
application/json  

Select event:
“Just the push event” → Add webhook.

Step-10: Configure Jenkins to Accept GitHub Webhooks
Jenkins Dashboard → Select Job → Configure → Build Triggers  
Enable:
☑ GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling  
Click Save.

Step-11: Test the Setup
Make any code update → push to GitHub → GitHub triggers webhook → Jenkins auto-builds.

Outcome:
GitHub and Jenkins connected successfully via Webhooks.  
Each push triggers an automatic Jenkins build.

---------------------------------------------------------------

EXERCISE-2 — Jenkins Email Notification Setup (Gmail App Password)

1. Gmail: Enable App Password
i. Go to https://myaccount.google.com  
ii. Enable:
Security → 2-Step Verification  
Complete OTP steps  
iii. Generate App Password:
Security → App Passwords  
App: Other (Custom Name)  
Name: Jenkins-Demo  
Click Generate → Copy 16-digit app password.

2. Jenkins Plugin Installation
i. Jenkins Dashboard  
ii. Manage Jenkins → Manage Plugins  
iii. Install:
Email Extension Plugin

3. Configure Jenkins Global Email Settings
i. Manage Jenkins → Configure System

A. Email Notification Section:
SMTP Server: smtp.gmail.com  
Use SMTP Auth: Enabled  
User Name: Your Gmail  
Password: 16-digit App Password  
Use SSL: Enabled  
SMTP Port: 465  
Reply-To: Same Gmail  
Test configuration → send test email.

B. Extended E-mail Notification:
SMTP Server: smtp.gmail.com  
SMTP Port: 465  
Use SSL: Enabled  
Credentials: Add Gmail + App Password  
Default Content Type: text/html  
Default Recipients: Optional  
Triggers: As required

4. Configure Email for a Jenkins Job
Job → Configure → Post-build Actions → Editable Email Notification  
Fill:
Project Recipient List  
Content Type  
Triggers  
Attachments (optional)

Click Save.

Takeaway:
Students learned GitHub → Jenkins Webhook integration AND Jenkins email notification setup.

